e 162 slac ucla usc home news brief overview collaborators notes and papers links welcome to the home page for the e 162 experiment at slac take a look at our news page for the most recent updates the e 162 experiment at slac is a continuation of the e 157 experiment we aim to extend high gradient plasma wakefield acceleration from the mm scale to the m scale an accelerating gradient of up to 1 gev m will be induced in a 1.4 m long plasma module using the high power slac linac beam the experiment will measure decelaration acceleration and transverse focusing of the injected bunch
